WEBVTT

00:15.750 --> 00:20.319
<i> - I never thought I'd die</i>
<i> by the moon like this.</i>

00:20.321 --> 00:23.722
<i> I thought I'd die</i>
<i> by poison kiss.</i>

00:23.724 --> 00:27.493
<i> On my way out of town,</i>
<i> roof all the way down.</i>

00:27.495 --> 00:31.096
<i> But me and you and everyone</i>
<i> are over and done.</i>

00:31.098 --> 00:33.732
<i> Chips off the old block</i>
<i> of a rock in the sky</i>

00:33.734 --> 00:35.701
<i> will rain on down.</i>

00:35.703 --> 00:38.437
<i> We got 36 hours</i>
<i> to get out of town.</i>

00:38.439 --> 00:40.305
<i> But there's nowhere to go.</i>

00:40.307 --> 00:43.509
<i> So love who you love</i>
<i> and remove all your doubt.</i>

00:43.511 --> 00:45.277
<i> Let your last times roll on.</i>

00:45.279 --> 00:48.347
<i> Let your madness roll out.</i>

00:49.450 --> 00:52.351
<i> - [murmuring indistinctly]</i>

00:53.521 --> 00:58.123
<i> There's two of her.</i>

00:58.125 --> 01:00.192
<i> Yeah, she'll be riding six</i>
<i> white horses when she comes.</i>

01:00.194 --> 01:02.594
There's two of her!
[laughing]

01:02.596 --> 01:05.497
[groaning]

01:06.634 --> 01:08.600
Ponaturi's gonna get you.

01:08.602 --> 01:10.669
Ponaturi's gonna get you!
Ponaturi's gonna get you!

01:10.671 --> 01:12.438
- All right.
All right.

01:12.440 --> 01:14.239
Listen to my voice.
It's Karen, Josh.

01:14.241 --> 01:15.641
- Karen.
I should've married that girl.

01:15.643 --> 01:17.676
- Yep.
You did.

01:17.678 --> 01:19.778
- Is there anything I can do?

01:19.780 --> 01:21.814
- [grunting]

01:21.816 --> 01:24.650
[speaking incoherently]

01:24.652 --> 01:26.452
- Okay.
Shh.

01:26.454 --> 01:27.619
- I'm getting out of here!

01:27.621 --> 01:29.721
- Okay.
- Lie down. Lie down.

01:29.723 --> 01:31.190
- Daddy?
- I'm not lying down.

01:31.192 --> 01:34.493
- Daddy?
Daddy, Daddy, shh.

01:36.664 --> 01:40.466
Do you remember
when I was little

01:40.468 --> 01:43.168
and I couldn't sleep,

01:43.170 --> 01:46.238
and you'd come into my room
and lay with me?

01:46.240 --> 01:49.141
- Oh. Oh.
- It's just like that.

01:49.143 --> 01:50.776
- Do you remember that?

01:50.778 --> 01:52.811
- Babies are sleeping.
- That's right. They are.

01:52.813 --> 01:54.279
- Shh.

01:55.416 --> 01:57.316
- Babies are sleeping.

01:57.318 --> 02:00.719
- [crying] I can't do this.
I can't watch this.

02:00.721 --> 02:01.787
- Babies are...

02:01.789 --> 02:03.422
- We have to get tetra.
- Where?

02:03.424 --> 02:05.190
Everywhere we've looked
is looted for miles.

02:05.192 --> 02:06.458
- I found propofol.
- What is it?

02:06.460 --> 02:07.726
- It's an anesthetic.

02:07.728 --> 02:09.261
- We're gonna give him
an anesthetic?

02:09.263 --> 02:11.230
- It'll put him
into a medically induced coma.

02:11.232 --> 02:14.199
- Well, you're a doctor now?

02:14.201 --> 02:15.267
- We have to try something.

02:15.269 --> 02:17.870
- Dana, we can't put him
into a coma.

02:17.872 --> 02:19.872
- He's a danger to others,
including us, Bree.

02:19.874 --> 02:21.640
- No, he's not.

02:21.642 --> 02:23.675
- At the very least,
he's a danger to himself.

02:23.677 --> 02:25.477
- True.
- If we put him under,

02:25.479 --> 02:27.146
it could slow down the disease,
and it gives us time

02:27.148 --> 02:28.814
to find tetra.

02:28.816 --> 02:31.717
- This is really dangerous.
And we need syringes.

02:31.719 --> 02:34.553
- I got those too.

02:34.555 --> 02:36.922
- Of course.

02:36.924 --> 02:40.192
If we give him too much,
he could die.

02:40.194 --> 02:42.694
- What do you think he's doing
right now?

02:42.696 --> 02:45.631
<i> [eerie music]</i>

02:45.633 --> 02:48.667
- I can't tell what's happening.

02:48.669 --> 02:50.903
<i> - We don't know what's</i>
<i> happening yet, Christine,</i>

02:50.905 --> 02:53.205
<i> but panic has swept the city</i>
<i> for ten minutes now, and--</i>

02:53.207 --> 02:55.340
<i> - Go!</i>
<i> Get out of here!</i>

02:55.342 --> 02:57.276
<i> - Oh, my God.</i>

02:57.278 --> 03:00.212
<i> And who will say that--</i>

03:00.214 --> 03:03.482
<i> oh, my God.</i>
<i> Are those people?</i>

03:03.484 --> 03:05.918
<i> No, no, don't tell me</i>
<i> those are people.</i>

03:05.920 --> 03:07.586
<i> Oh, my God, it's here!</i>

03:07.588 --> 03:10.389
<i> Oh, Jesus, it's here!</i>
<i> Aah!</i>

03:10.391 --> 03:11.957
<i> Tell everyone it's here!</i>

03:11.959 --> 03:15.427
Oh, my God.
Are those people?

03:15.429 --> 03:17.663
No, no, don't tell me
those are people.

03:17.665 --> 03:19.531
Oh, my God, it's here!

03:19.533 --> 03:21.667
Oh, Jesus, it's here!
Aah!

03:21.669 --> 03:23.835
Tell everyone it's here!

03:23.837 --> 03:26.438
But the many are one!

03:26.440 --> 03:28.273
[exhales]

03:28.275 --> 03:30.375
But the many are one.

03:30.377 --> 03:32.377
What, where--

03:32.379 --> 03:35.347
<i> [ominous music]</i>

03:35.349 --> 03:42.287
<i> ♪</i> ♪

03:43.657 --> 03:47.259
What--oh, God.

03:47.261 --> 03:48.694
Okay.

03:48.696 --> 03:50.395
But the many are one.

03:50.397 --> 03:52.965
[breathing heavily]
But the many--

03:52.967 --> 03:56.902
but the many--but the many--
but the many are one?

03:56.904 --> 03:59.538
But the many--

03:59.540 --> 04:01.273
- Got you.

04:01.275 --> 04:03.308
- Where'd you come from?

04:03.310 --> 04:04.776
- Seattle.
- Bullshit.

04:04.778 --> 04:06.612
- How'd you get here?
- I don't know.

04:06.614 --> 04:09.414
I--I don't remember.

04:09.416 --> 04:10.782
- You're coming with us.
- No. No, I'm not.

04:10.784 --> 04:12.251
- You're showing signs
of plague.

04:12.253 --> 04:13.986
We don't let Feverheads in.
Come on.

04:13.988 --> 04:15.354
- No!
Who are you people?

04:15.356 --> 04:16.888
- Board of Health.
- What?

04:16.890 --> 04:18.023
- Let's go!
- No! What?

04:18.025 --> 04:19.891
- Come on!
- Oh, God.

04:21.795 --> 04:23.895
- Come on.

04:23.897 --> 04:25.430
- Let's go.
Let's go.

04:32.640 --> 04:34.906
- His breathing's fine. That's
what we need to watch out for.

04:34.908 --> 04:36.341
- How do you know that?

04:36.343 --> 04:37.676
- Michael Jackson's
autopsy report.

04:37.678 --> 04:39.044
- You don't like
Michael Jackson.

04:39.046 --> 04:40.912
- No, but I like
autopsy reports.

04:40.914 --> 04:44.850
- Okay, Matt and I are gonna
go find tetra or die trying.

04:44.852 --> 04:46.818
Figure of speech.

04:46.820 --> 04:50.355
You guys stay here,
keep your dad breathing,

04:50.357 --> 04:51.757
and be careful.

04:57.765 --> 05:00.499
- If he starts to wake up,
we may have to give him more.

05:00.501 --> 05:03.502
- As little as possible, Dana.

05:03.504 --> 05:05.404
- Yeah, of course.

05:11.779 --> 05:13.478
- Don't worry.
It's gonna be fine.

05:20.688 --> 05:23.021
[gunfire]
- [screams]

05:23.023 --> 05:24.890
- Doc!

05:24.892 --> 05:26.725
Doc, it's us.

05:26.727 --> 05:28.827
We got one!

05:28.829 --> 05:30.729
- Please, you have to help me!

05:30.731 --> 05:31.963
- Shut up.

05:37.805 --> 05:39.371
- Where'd you find her?

05:39.373 --> 05:42.441
- Peach Street.
Those abandoned houses.

05:42.443 --> 05:44.343
- She doesn't look sick.
- I'm not sick.

05:44.345 --> 05:46.445
- She was talking weird.
Says she came from Seattle.

05:46.447 --> 05:48.880
- I am. I am.
I'm from Seattle.

05:48.882 --> 05:51.817
- All right.
I'll examine her.

05:51.819 --> 05:53.385
Right this way, Miss Seattle.

05:53.387 --> 05:55.721
- No, no, no,
you have no right.

05:55.723 --> 05:57.489
- I've got all the right
in the world.

05:57.491 --> 06:00.359
- What?
Oh, okay, okay, okay.

06:00.361 --> 06:03.095
[whimpering]

06:08.502 --> 06:09.768
[door slams]

06:09.770 --> 06:11.536
- Think we'll get to do it?

06:11.538 --> 06:13.705
- It's up to the doc.
Let's keep looking.

06:13.707 --> 06:14.873
- All right.

06:20.881 --> 06:23.749
- We're okay.
For now.

06:23.751 --> 06:26.017
- This is weird, Dana.

06:26.019 --> 06:28.787
Us watching him when he's sick.

06:28.789 --> 06:30.155
- Role reversal.

06:30.157 --> 06:31.790
- Do you remember
when we were little

06:31.792 --> 06:34.659
and we got hoof and mouth
disease?

06:34.661 --> 06:36.995
- Hand, foot, and mouth disease.

06:36.997 --> 06:38.697
- I don't know.
- Not that it sounds any better.

06:38.699 --> 06:41.533
- What, we were, like,
six, maybe?

06:41.535 --> 06:44.169
- Seven.
- Such a pain in the ass.

06:44.171 --> 06:47.005
- Hey, someone's got
to keep things straight.

06:49.076 --> 06:50.142
- You remember how you were,

06:50.144 --> 06:52.711
like, super scared
to fall asleep

06:52.713 --> 06:55.847
because you thought if you did
you were gonna die?

06:55.849 --> 06:58.049
- I got bad information.

06:58.051 --> 07:01.887
- And then Dad would come in and
lay on the floor of our room.

07:06.794 --> 07:08.160
- Yeah.

07:10.697 --> 07:12.831
- Didn't he tell us, like,

07:12.833 --> 07:16.601
a story about a spider invasion
or something?

07:16.603 --> 07:18.203
- [laughs]
"Charlotte's Web"?

07:18.205 --> 07:21.506
- I don't know.
I was so sick.

07:21.508 --> 07:23.642
And we were, like,
six years old.

07:23.644 --> 07:26.711
- Seven.
- Same thing.

07:26.713 --> 07:30.048
- Dad always had
the best stories.

07:30.050 --> 07:33.185
- Yeah, he did.

07:33.187 --> 07:34.619
A lot of creepy myths, though.

07:34.621 --> 07:35.821
- [laughs]

07:41.128 --> 07:45.931
- Dana, do you really think
he's gonna be okay?

07:45.933 --> 07:49.501
- Yeah.
Yeah, he has to be.

07:58.178 --> 07:59.945
- There's a hospital
down that way

07:59.947 --> 08:01.913
and a drug store down that way.
- I'd rather not split up.

08:01.915 --> 08:04.015
- We're gonna have to
if we want to cover everything.

08:04.017 --> 08:06.485
- Yeah. Okay.
- I'll take the hospital.

08:06.487 --> 08:08.487
You take the drug store.
We'll meet back here at the car.

08:08.489 --> 08:11.923
- Got it.
Let's...

08:11.925 --> 08:14.526
have a sign.

08:14.528 --> 08:16.828
You find the tetra,
you don't wait for me.

08:16.830 --> 08:18.663
You put this in the windshield.
- Okay, good.

08:18.665 --> 08:19.931
- I'll know you're at home.

08:19.933 --> 08:21.066
- You do the same.

08:21.068 --> 08:22.767
- Got it.
You be careful.

08:22.769 --> 08:24.569
- You too.

08:27.574 --> 08:29.808
- Okay.

08:29.810 --> 08:32.911
Let's get you nice
and comfortable.

08:35.716 --> 08:37.282
Any fever or vomiting?

08:37.284 --> 08:40.986
- No.
- Feel sick at all?

08:40.988 --> 08:44.689
- No. I just keep hearing
the same words over and over.

08:44.691 --> 08:46.124
- And what's that?

08:46.126 --> 08:48.793
- But the many are one.

08:48.795 --> 08:50.762
- What was that?

08:50.764 --> 08:52.731
- But the many are one.

08:52.733 --> 08:55.000
- Huh.
That's different.

08:57.738 --> 09:00.972
Okay, let's take a look inside.

09:02.242 --> 09:03.842
Open wide.

09:08.048 --> 09:09.281
Huh.

09:11.718 --> 09:13.919
Well, there's no blood.

09:13.921 --> 09:15.720
I'd say you're clear.

09:15.722 --> 09:17.956
- Clear?
Clear of what?

09:17.958 --> 09:19.891
- Plague.

09:19.893 --> 09:21.626
- What kind of plague?

09:23.096 --> 09:25.564
- Where you been?

09:25.566 --> 09:27.098
- I wish I knew.

09:27.100 --> 09:29.668
- Brain fever.

09:29.670 --> 09:33.104
The rumor is 1/3 of the
Earth has already died from it.

09:33.106 --> 09:35.073
Our town was just about
wiped out,

09:35.075 --> 09:38.777
so if you had been sick...

09:38.779 --> 09:41.146
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

09:41.148 --> 09:43.148
It wouldn't be good.

09:43.150 --> 09:45.116
- What does that mean?

09:45.118 --> 09:47.018
- Well, we can't have any chance
of infection,

09:47.020 --> 09:50.088
so we round up
any Feverheads we find, and--

09:50.090 --> 09:51.656
- Force them out of town?

09:51.658 --> 09:54.059
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:54.061 --> 09:55.327
- Eliminate them.

09:57.798 --> 10:00.599
- And--and you're in charge
of this?

10:00.601 --> 10:03.602
- Last surviving medical man.

10:03.604 --> 10:06.037
So you say you came here
from Seattle?

10:06.039 --> 10:07.772
- Yeah.

10:07.774 --> 10:09.207
- Well, Seattle's gone.

10:12.079 --> 10:13.845
- Gone?

10:13.847 --> 10:16.781
What do you mean, "gone"?

10:16.783 --> 10:18.883
- I mean the buildings
are there. The people are gone.

10:18.885 --> 10:20.685
- I was one of those people.
What happened?

10:20.687 --> 10:21.786
I--

10:21.788 --> 10:24.689
how did I end up in--

10:24.691 --> 10:25.957
where are we?

10:25.959 --> 10:27.993
- Idaho.

10:27.995 --> 10:30.762
- How did I end up in Idaho?

10:30.764 --> 10:32.030
- Beats me.

10:32.032 --> 10:35.033
- I--

10:35.035 --> 10:37.035
I got to--
I got to get out of here.

10:37.037 --> 10:38.837
I, uh--

10:38.839 --> 10:40.972
I need to know what's going on.

10:40.974 --> 10:43.808
- Oh, ah-ah-ah-ah.

10:43.810 --> 10:45.410
Look.
If I were you,

10:45.412 --> 10:48.647
I would consider moving on.

10:48.649 --> 10:51.049
It's not a good time
for strangers around here.

10:51.051 --> 10:57.989
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:13.874 --> 11:15.273
[sniffs]

11:17.077 --> 11:19.778
- [breathing heavily]
Okay.

11:19.780 --> 11:21.797
Oh, God.

11:21.798 --> 11:23.815
<i> - What is taking them so long?</i>
<i> - Tetra's hard to find.</i>

11:23.817 --> 11:25.884
- Then there should be
more of us looking, Dana.

11:25.886 --> 11:28.887
- Well, we can't leave Dad.
- Yeah, you can't. I can.

11:28.889 --> 11:31.322
- Oh, no, no. No, do not start
with this, Bree.

11:31.324 --> 11:34.392
- Dana, I am useless here, okay?
You know what you're doing.

11:34.394 --> 11:36.761
- Not really.
- Well, more than I do.

11:39.433 --> 11:41.099
That's it.
I'm gonna go look.

11:41.101 --> 11:43.868
- How?
- There's a car in the driveway.

11:43.870 --> 11:46.304
- You don't have the keys.
- Then I'll hotwire it.

11:46.306 --> 11:47.872
- You know how to do that?

11:47.874 --> 11:49.841
- Fortunately, yes, I do.

11:49.843 --> 11:52.243
Keep our dad alive.
Safety's off.

11:52.245 --> 11:55.413
- Don't do this.
- Take the gun, Dana.

11:58.318 --> 12:01.786
- I'll be back.
- Come on, Bree.

12:01.788 --> 12:03.288
[sighs]
[door clicks]

12:03.290 --> 12:06.024
- [groans]

12:06.026 --> 12:08.860
- No, no, no, no.
Come on.

12:08.862 --> 12:11.796
Come on, Dad,
please stay asleep.

12:14.868 --> 12:17.936
- [mumbling]

12:17.938 --> 12:20.338
<i> [swelling dramatic music]</i>

12:22.109 --> 12:25.977
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

12:25.979 --> 12:27.512
- Come on, tetra.

12:27.514 --> 12:29.080
Come on!

12:31.752 --> 12:33.118
- Elizabeth!

12:33.120 --> 12:34.853
Lizzie!

12:34.855 --> 12:36.187
- No, I'm not--I'm not--
- Have you seen Barry?

12:36.189 --> 12:37.856
You're not Elizabeth.
- No. Sorry.

12:37.858 --> 12:40.425
- You look like her.
I'm so stupid.

12:40.427 --> 12:42.861
- No, no, don't.
Don't worry about it.

12:42.863 --> 12:45.897
- She's dead now.
Weeks ago.

12:45.899 --> 12:47.932
- It's terrible times.
- Family and friends--

12:47.934 --> 12:49.217
- Tetracycline.
Do you have tetracycline

12:49.218 --> 12:50.501
or know where I can get some?
- Most of this town died

12:50.504 --> 12:51.870
of plague.
There's none left.

12:51.871 --> 12:53.237
But have you seen my husband?
- No. Sorry.

12:53.240 --> 12:54.806
- He's my age.
Pajamas.

12:54.808 --> 12:56.474
His glasses are broken,
taped together.

12:56.476 --> 12:58.143
- Yeah, I'm sorry. I got to go.
- His name's Barry.

12:58.145 --> 12:59.244
- Okay. I'm sorry.
- He's acting strange,

12:59.246 --> 13:00.879
but he doesn't have plague.

13:00.881 --> 13:02.213
- Well, that's a good thing,
right?

13:02.215 --> 13:03.148
- See, he went to Seattle
on business.

13:03.150 --> 13:05.917
- Please.
Please.

13:05.919 --> 13:08.153
He went to Seattle?
- I didn't see him for weeks.

13:08.155 --> 13:10.288
People say Seattle's gone.

13:10.290 --> 13:12.056
- Yeah. Yeah.
Empty, actually.

13:12.058 --> 13:14.125
- Some say it was the rapture,

13:14.127 --> 13:16.895
but Seattle's not all that holy
that they'd get taken up.

13:16.897 --> 13:18.963
- Right.
- But--but I was right.

13:18.965 --> 13:21.332
Barry came back last night.
- Honey, I got to go.

13:21.334 --> 13:23.568
- Barry came back!

13:23.570 --> 13:25.370
- What do you mean he came back?

13:25.372 --> 13:30.241
- In bed. With me.
I never even heard him come in.

13:30.243 --> 13:32.076
- He came back?
- He doesn't remember anything,

13:32.078 --> 13:33.378
and he says something's coming!

13:38.451 --> 13:40.285
He's--he's all worked up--
- I got to go! I got to go!

13:40.287 --> 13:42.954
- And he says
something's coming!

13:52.532 --> 13:53.865
- Shit.

13:53.867 --> 13:55.867
- [gasping]

13:55.869 --> 13:57.969
- Hold on!
[gunshots]

13:57.971 --> 13:59.237
- [gasping]

13:59.239 --> 14:00.238
[gunshot]

14:00.240 --> 14:01.339
[screams]

14:02.509 --> 14:04.342
You bastard!

14:04.344 --> 14:06.110
- Just take it--hey!
Easy! Relax!

14:06.112 --> 14:07.612
- Get off me!
- Stop! I'm trying to help you.

14:07.614 --> 14:09.547
- I don't want to be sick!
Get off me!

14:09.549 --> 14:11.916
- I'm trying--hey!
Hey!

14:11.918 --> 14:13.451
I'm trying to help you!

14:20.527 --> 14:23.294
- Yeah, there's no denying
of what we saw today.

14:23.296 --> 14:24.429
- Ugh.

14:24.431 --> 14:26.531
[screeching]
[gunshot]

14:26.533 --> 14:28.333
- Honey!
- [shouts indistinctly]

14:28.335 --> 14:31.302
<i> - The two guys in the jail.</i>

14:31.304 --> 14:34.239
<i> - Oh, no, no,</i>
<i> there was nothing inside them.</i>

14:34.241 --> 14:36.574
<i> They were just batshit crazy.</i>

