<i> [intense music]</i>

21:38.831 --> 21:39.897
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:39.899 --> 21:42.767
<i> [garbled beeping noises]</i>

21:54.881 --> 21:56.514
- What is happening?

21:58.084 --> 21:59.984
What is happening?
Do you know?

21:59.986 --> 22:02.653
- No.

22:02.655 --> 22:04.789
- Okay, your husband.

22:04.791 --> 22:07.391
I need your help.
I need your help.

22:07.393 --> 22:09.327
Can you help me?
Your husband knew something.

22:09.329 --> 22:11.962
I need to know what it is.
What did he tell you?

22:11.964 --> 22:15.966
- That the white whirlwind--
the white whirlwind.

22:15.968 --> 22:17.902
- Okay. It had a sound.
I heard it.

22:17.904 --> 22:19.937
- You heard it?
- Yeah, it was on footage

22:19.939 --> 22:22.840
from, um--
footage from Seattle.

22:22.842 --> 22:24.508
My husband showed me.

22:24.510 --> 22:27.445
- He was there?
- Your husband was in Seattle.

22:27.447 --> 22:28.779
- Yes.
- When everyone disappeared.

22:28.781 --> 22:30.348
- Yes.
- But he--but he came back.

22:30.350 --> 22:32.683
He disappeared
and he came back.

22:32.685 --> 22:34.785
- Yes.
- For you.

22:34.787 --> 22:36.687
- Yes.

22:36.689 --> 22:38.356
- Tell me why.

22:38.358 --> 22:40.725
Why?

22:40.727 --> 22:42.493
Why?
- Someone knows something.

22:42.495 --> 22:44.428
- Okay.
Okay.

22:44.430 --> 22:47.398
- And they need to tell us
what's happening.

22:47.400 --> 22:49.633
- I think it's my husband.

22:49.635 --> 22:50.768
- Yes.

22:50.770 --> 22:52.603
[crying]

22:52.605 --> 22:54.138
- It's my husband.

22:54.140 --> 22:57.375
Okay?
I have to keep him alive.

22:57.377 --> 22:58.776
- Yes.

22:58.778 --> 23:00.978
- Thank you.
I have to go.

23:02.915 --> 23:04.415
He's my husband.

23:06.552 --> 23:07.718
Okay.

23:21.033 --> 23:22.566
- Shh.

23:24.837 --> 23:27.405
[laughs]

23:27.407 --> 23:29.774
- I know where there's drugs.
- What?

23:29.776 --> 23:32.476
- You said you wanted drugs?

23:32.478 --> 23:34.912
I didn't say anything because we
were keeping it for ourselves.

23:34.914 --> 23:37.114
- Who's we?
- Me and my sister.

23:37.116 --> 23:38.983
We're squatting at a house
just east of here.

23:38.985 --> 23:41.485
- Not impressed.
- Yeah. This city's dead.

23:41.487 --> 23:43.020
There's, like, plenty of squats.

23:43.022 --> 23:45.156
- No, no, this guy--
this guy was a drug hound, man.

23:45.158 --> 23:48.092
We couldn't get through the
stash in a month if we tried.

23:48.094 --> 23:49.660
- Why you telling us this?

23:49.662 --> 23:52.830
- Because I'm offering you
a trade.

23:52.832 --> 23:54.565
You get the shit.

23:54.567 --> 23:56.033
My sis and I walk.

23:56.035 --> 23:58.769
Deal?

23:58.771 --> 24:00.471
- Cool.
Let's go trade.

24:00.473 --> 24:01.906
To the car.

24:01.908 --> 24:04.074
- Drugs!
Let's get those drugs!

24:04.076 --> 24:05.843
- Cars are the chief exemplar

24:05.845 --> 24:07.645
of the destructive consumer
society.

24:07.647 --> 24:09.713
[grunts]
Cut it out.

24:09.715 --> 24:11.949
- You're lying,
you're dying.

24:13.152 --> 24:15.586
- Hi.

24:15.588 --> 24:17.087
- Hi.
- I should've told you earlier.

24:17.089 --> 24:18.823
You were really good to me.
I wasn't thinking.

24:18.825 --> 24:20.524
- Told me what?
- Kimmy, that girl I--

24:20.526 --> 24:21.659
- You made a mistake.

24:21.661 --> 24:22.827
- Yeah.
